Explanation

This problem is to find the strongest team in a tournament. Each team has a unique index, and the teams are numbered from 0 to n - 1. In the tournament, if team i beats team j, then the element at grid[i][j] is 1, and the element at grid[j][i] is 0. The team that does not lose any match is the champion of the tournament.

The idea is to check each team one by one, and see if it is the champion. To check if a team is the champion, we need to check if there is any other team that beats it. If there is no such team, then the current team is the champion.

To check if a team is the champion, we need to check if there is any other team that beats it. We can do this by checking if the element at grid[i][j] is 1 and the element at grid[j][i] is 0 for all i != j. If there is such a team, then the current team is not the champion, and we can continue to the next team. If there is no such team, then the current team is the champion, and we can return the team number.

We need to check all n teams in the tournament to find the champion. If we find a champion, we can return its team number immediately. If we cannot find a champion, then we can return -1.

Time Complexity: O(n^2)

Space Complexity: O(1)

